<chapter id="perl-modules">
<?dbhtml filename="@DOC_DIR@/admin/perl-modules.html" ?>
<title>GridShib-CA Perl Modules</title>
 
<para>
Starting with version 0.3.0 the GridShib-CA used a number of PERL
modules to implement run-time behavior. While the GridShib-CA deploys
a set of modules by default, they can be changed using
the <ulink url="install.html#gridshib-ca.conf">gridshib-ca.conf</ulink>
configuration file. A list of modules and the parameter used to
specific the module loaded is given below.
</para>
<table tocentry="0">
<title>GridShib-CA Perl Modules</title>
<tgroup cols="3">
<thead>
<row>
<entry>Module</entry>
<entry>Configuration parameter</entry>
<entry>Notes</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/Authorization.html">Authorization</ulink></entry>
<entry>Authorization</entry>
<entry>Authorizes user.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/CA.html">CA</ulink></entry>
<entry>CA</entry>
<entry>Template. Default implementation is
	currently <ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/OpenSSLCA.html">OpenSSLCA.pm</ulink>.
	A <ulink url="myproxy-ca.html">MyProxy-based CA</ulink> is also available
	with <ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/MyProxyCA.html">MyProxyCA.pm</ulink>.
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/CertRegistry.html">CertRegistry</ulink></entry>
<entry>certRegistryModule</entry>
<entry>Wrapper around Certificate Registry module. Other implementations
	include <ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/myVocsDBCertRegistry.html">myVocsDBCertRegistry.pm</ulink></entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/CGIinterface.html">CGIinterface</ulink></entry>
<entry>CGI</entry>
<entry>Wrapper around PERL CGI module</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/CGISession.html">CGISession</ulink></entry>
<entry>CGISession</entry>
<entry>Wrapper around PERL CGI::Session module</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/Command.html">Command</ulink></entry>
<entry>commandModule</entry>
<entry>Interface to executing system commands, controlling their input
	and getting their output</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/Logger.html">Logger</ulink></entry>
<entry>Logger</entry>
<entry>Interface to logging mechanism. Default implementation uses
	syslog.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/NameMapper.html">NameMapper</ulink></entry>
<entry>NameMapper</entry>
<entry>Maps from Shibboleth authentication/attributes to X.509 DN.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/SAMLExtension.html">SAMLExtension</ulink></entry>
<entry>SAMLExtension</entry>
<entry>Module to generate SAML extension for certificate.</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/TokenGenerator.html">TokenGenerator</ulink></entry>
<entry>TokenGenerator</entry>
<entry>Used to generate Tokens used to authenticate user requests</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry><ulink url="perl/GridShibCA/WebSignOn.html">WebSignOn</ulink></entry>
<entry>WebSignOn</entry>
<entry>Template. Default is <ulink
url="perl/GridShibCA/ShibSignOn.html">ShibSignOn</ulink>. Other option
is <ulink
url="perl/GridShibCA/FakeSignOn.html">FakeSignOn</ulink>.</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>

</chapter>
